to this first ever symposium

00:00:36.180 --> 00:00:39.840
on the Sasanian Empire, here
at the Library of Congress.

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:43.960
Thank you Congressmen
Raskin for taking the time

00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:46.000
from your very busy
schedule to be with us.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:50.330
I'm Mary-Jane Deeb, Chief of the
African and Middle East Division.

00:00:50.330 --> 00:00:54.090
This division has organized
this conference here

00:00:54.090 --> 00:00:56.300
in the Thomas Jefferson
building of the Library.

00:00:56.300 --> 00:01:02.750
And this symposium is
part of an annual series

00:01:02.750 --> 00:01:06.990
that this division holds on
the ancient civilizations

00:01:06.990 --> 00:01:11.640
of the Middle East that go
back many thousands of years.

