coordinating the libraries work the

00:01:46.440 --> 00:01:51.180
Unites States Newspaper Program,
a cooperative national effort

00:01:51.180 --> 00:01:55.730
to locate, catalogue, and preserve
microfilm newspapers published

00:01:55.730 --> 00:01:58.620
in the United States from the
18th Century to the present.

00:01:58.620 --> 00:02:01.570
So, you can imagine
how many millions

00:02:01.570 --> 00:02:06.690
of pages were preserved that way.

00:02:06.690 --> 00:02:09.260
The following year, he
was selected to be chief

00:02:09.260 --> 00:02:12.140
of the Library's Preservation
and Reformatting Division.

00:02:12.140 --> 00:02:14.650
He then became Chief
of the Humanities

00:02:14.650 --> 00:02:15.980
and Social Science Division.

00:02:15.980 --> 00:02:20.410
And in 2012 he became
Director of Preservation.

00:02:20.410 --> 00:02:24.740
Three years later in 2015, he
was appointed by the Librarian

00:02:24.740 --> 00:02:28.710
of Congress as Associate
Librarian of Library Services.

00:02:28.710 --> 00:02:32.450
Mark Sweeney earned a Bachelor of
Arts degree from McGill University

00:02:32.450 --> 00:02:36.130
on Montreal, Canada and a
Master's Degree in Library Science

00:02:36.130 --> 00:02:37.890
from Catholic University.

00:02:37.890 --> 00:02:39.690
Mark Sweeney.

