Sasanian Empire.

00:03:06.260 --> 00:03:10.210
This symposium of the first one
ever held on the Sasanian Empire,

00:03:10.210 --> 00:03:15.080
the last of the major ancient
pre-Islamic Persian empires.

00:03:15.080 --> 00:03:18.900
The Sasanian Empire extended
from the near east to central

00:03:18.900 --> 00:03:23.150
and south Asian over a span
of more than 400 years.

00:03:23.150 --> 00:03:26.650
Furthermore, the empire
left a rich cultural legacy

00:03:26.650 --> 00:03:30.380
that shaped the region and defined
elements of Iranian identity

00:03:30.380 --> 00:03:33.960
that remain conspicuous
up to the present day.

00:03:33.960 --> 00:03:35.260
The holdings of the Library

00:03:35.260 --> 00:03:38.540
of Congress include the world's
largest collection of books,

00:03:38.540 --> 00:03:42.430
monographs, serials, maps,
and many other materials

00:03:42.430 --> 00:03:45.050
about the Sasanian period.

00:03:45.050 --> 00:03:48.850
Today you will find a selection
of these items from the collection

00:03:48.850 --> 00:03:52.490
on display in the African and
Middle Eastern conference room here

00:03:52.490 --> 00:03:57.010
in the Thomas Jefferson
building through those doors.

