So, you built this wall, you
have this sort of physical space.

00:40:18.040 --> 00:40:19.340
So, who dwells in it?

00:40:19.340 --> 00:40:20.640
Who should?

00:40:20.640 --> 00:40:22.430
And who should stay
out of this paradise?

00:40:22.430 --> 00:40:26.510 position:56%
And I think the Persian tiles from
much later on and the carpet itself.

00:40:26.510 --> 00:40:31.380 position:56%
The Persian carpets really sort of
bring forth this idea of a paradise.

00:40:31.380 --> 00:40:32.680
This garden.

00:40:32.680 --> 00:40:33.980
And that is part of
this part of this sort

00:40:33.980 --> 00:40:36.500
of Persian heritage
of a Persian garden.

00:40:36.500 --> 00:40:37.800
Mimicking it.

00:40:37.800 --> 00:40:40.400
Even when the king sits on
a carpet within a garden.

00:40:40.400 --> 00:40:43.690
That again is part
of that tradition.

00:40:43.690 --> 00:40:47.080
Now, just to point out that
