00:49:34.990 --> 00:49:40.170
The caucuses is the
stuff of legends.

00:49:40.170 --> 00:49:44.090
Jews, Christians, and Muslims
imagined its towering spires

00:49:44.090 --> 00:49:48.190
as the resting place of Noah's
Ark after the great deluge.

00:49:48.190 --> 00:49:52.500
Humanity repopulated the
earth from this second Eden.

00:49:52.500 --> 00:49:54.490 position:56%
The Ancient Greeks regarded Caucasia

00:49:54.490 --> 00:49:59.370
as an exotic nearly inaccessible
land at the edge of the world.

00:49:59.370 --> 00:50:02.720
Jason and the Argonauts
peruse the Golden Fleece here.

00:50:02.720 --> 00:50:05.080
And Prometheus had
been chained to a rock

00:50:05.080 --> 00:50:08.100
in the foreboding Caucuses
mountains as punishment

00:50:08.100 --> 00:50:11.400
for stealing fire from Mt. Olympus.

00:50:11.400 --> 00:50:14.950
Caucasia's association with fire
is an old one thanks in part

00:50:14.950 --> 00:50:20.640 position:56%
to the petroleum deposits literally
seeping to the ground in Azerbaijan.

00:50:20.640 --> 00:50:23.100
Some scholars have even
proposed Azerbaijan

00:50:23.100 --> 00:50:28.040
as the primordial homeland
of Zoroastrianism.

00:50:28.040 --> 00:50:29.340
The isthmus between the Black

00:50:29.340 --> 00:50:31.850
and Caspian seas is
simultaneously been regarded

00:50:31.850 --> 00:50:35.250
as an exotic and hazardous place.

00:50:35.250 --> 00:50:39.780
Pre-Islamic Iranians envisioned
Caucasia as the habitat of demons

00:50:39.780 --> 00:50:42.160
on the edge of the garden
we just heard about.

00:50:42.160 --> 00:50:44.120
The menacing north.

00:50:44.120 --> 00:50:47.270
The great monotheisms of North
Afro-Eurasia perpetuated this

00:50:47.270 --> 00:50:52.390
northern dread in the apocalyptic
prophesy of Gog and Magog.

00:50:52.390 --> 00:50:56.940
Fierce uncivilized peoples whom at
the end of time Satan would unleash

00:50:56.940 --> 00:50:59.410
from their confinement behind
the great wall of rock,

00:50:59.410 --> 00:51:02.690
that is the Caucasus Mountains.

00:51:02.690 --> 00:51:04.900
The raising of this wall
was subsequently credited

00:51:04.900 --> 00:51:08.580
to the world conquer
Alexander the Great.

00:51:08.580 --> 00:51:13.040
Today, the Caucasus remains
the stuff of legends.

00:51:13.040 --> 00:51:16.600
In our part of the world it is a
region inspiring boundless wonder

00:51:16.600 --> 00:51:18.420
and horrific peril.

00:51:18.420 --> 00:51:22.360
It is conveniently far away from
the centers of Western Europe,

00:51:22.360 --> 00:51:26.830
yet in a globalizing world
it is not so distant at all.

00:51:26.830 --> 00:51:28.210
From this tension proceeds one

00:51:28.210 --> 00:51:31.660
of the most durable
modern images of Caucasia.

00:51:31.660 --> 00:51:35.570
It's location at the juncture
between East and West.

00:51:35.570 --> 00:51:39.320
This binary notion of ordering the
world with its undue privileging

00:51:39.320 --> 00:51:42.840
of the Euro-American experience
has been massively critiqued.

00:51:42.840 --> 00:51:46.780
As demonstrated by Edward
Said and numerous others,

00:51:46.780 --> 00:51:49.260 position:56%
East and west are the living residue

00:51:49.260 --> 00:51:52.240
of Europe's global
imperial colonial projects

00:51:52.240 --> 00:51:55.030
of the 19th and 20th Centuries.

00:51:55.030 --> 00:51:58.270
While convenient, such
met geographical concepts

00:51:58.270 --> 00:52:00.740
like East and West are slippery.

00:52:00.740 --> 00:52:04.170
They're saturated in
ideology and ethnocentrism

00:52:04.170 --> 00:52:08.330
and they are inherently
a-historical.

00:52:08.330 --> 00:52:09.840
Nevertheless, Caucasia is said

00:52:09.840 --> 00:52:14.200
to routinely occupy a space
between East and West.

00:52:14.200 --> 00:52:16.640
This morning I would like
to illustrate the fallacy

00:52:16.640 --> 00:52:20.140
of this stubborn projection
through written sources produced

00:52:20.140 --> 00:52:23.210
in the three kingdoms of
Late Antique Caucasia.

00:52:23.210 --> 00:52:28.110
Armenia Major, the Eastern Georgian
Realm of Chartley called <i>Hiberia</i>

00:52:28.110 --> 00:52:32.920
<i>in Greco Roman Sources</i>
, and Caucasian Albania.

00:52:32.920 --> 00:52:38.300 position:56%
If we accept Late Antique Caucasia's
position in the interstitial space

00:52:38.300 --> 00:52:42.200
between East and West then
it would have been located

00:52:42.200 --> 00:52:44.830
between the Greco Roman
Mediterranean

00:52:44.830 --> 00:52:47.990
on the one end and
Iran on the other.

00:52:47.990 --> 00:52:51.620 position:56%
But this is problematic in two ways.

00:52:51.620 --> 00:52:55.060
First, as a growing body of
scholarship is demonstrating --

00:52:55.060 --> 00:52:57.320
some of which was produced
by the scholars sitting

00:52:57.320 --> 00:53:00.080
in this very room today
-- the Greco Roman

00:53:00.080 --> 00:53:02.470
and Iranian worlds were
far more than imperial

00:53:02.470 --> 00:53:04.430
and civilizational competitors.

00:53:04.430 --> 00:53:05.970
And they were not isolated

00:53:05.970 --> 00:53:09.640
by definite static and
obvious boundaries.

00:53:09.640 --> 00:53:13.160
Instead, the two imperial
enterprises were tightly interwoven

00:53:13.160 --> 00:53:16.040
into a transcontinental
social, cultural,

00:53:16.040 --> 00:53:17.800
political, and economic web.

00:53:17.800 --> 00:53:22.660
What Peter Brown termed The
World of Late Antiquity.

00:53:22.660 --> 00:53:26.080
Such ties even encompass
models of imperial power.

00:53:26.080 --> 00:53:31.200
A second problem was seen as
Caucasia as space between worlds is

00:53:31.200 --> 00:53:34.340
that the isthmus has
been an enduring crucible

00:53:34.340 --> 00:53:37.790
across cultural encounter
throughout its lengthy history.

00:53:37.790 --> 00:53:41.160
When investigated from a
cross-cultural vantage,

00:53:41.160 --> 00:53:45.130
Caucasia emerges not as a
dangerous exotic periphery,

00:53:45.130 --> 00:53:49.250
but as one of Afro-Eurasia's
most dynamic centers alongside

00:53:49.250 --> 00:53:51.140
Central Asia.

00:53:51.140 --> 00:53:55.350
Approached as deploying a stringent
East/West divide undercut the

00:53:55.350 --> 00:54:00.300
cross-cultural interplay that is
the propellant of Late Antiquity.

00:54:00.300 --> 00:54:04.960
There are two main assumptions
underpinning Caucasia's affiliation

00:54:04.960 --> 00:54:06.440
with the West.

00:54:06.440 --> 00:54:10.540
Around the year 1800 the German
scholar Johann Blumenbach singled

00:54:10.540 --> 00:54:14.080
out skulls from Caucasia
and Georgia in particular

00:54:14.080 --> 00:54:18.190
as representing humanities
most important race.

00:54:18.190 --> 00:54:20.610
Ever since the Europeans
identification

00:54:20.610 --> 00:54:22.850
as principle modern members

00:54:22.850 --> 00:54:27.500
of the so-called Caucasian race
has lessened the mental distance

00:54:27.500 --> 00:54:30.630
between Europe and Caucasia.

00:54:30.630 --> 00:54:33.680
The second assumption proceeds
from the early Christianization

00:54:33.680 --> 00:54:38.790
of Southern Caucasia, archelogy
established Christianity's genuine

00:54:38.790 --> 00:54:43.670
presence in Caucasia no
later than the 3rd Century.

00:54:43.670 --> 00:54:45.720
In the 4th Century
the Dynastic monarchs

00:54:45.720 --> 00:54:49.420
of Caucasia's principle
realms Armenia Major,

00:54:49.420 --> 00:54:51.500
Carley in Eastern Georgia,

00:54:51.500 --> 00:54:55.300
and Albania all converted
to Christianity.

00:54:55.300 --> 00:54:58.720
By the 5th Century various strands
of Christianity were dominant

00:54:58.720 --> 00:55:01.400
across the Caucasian isthmus.

00:55:01.400 --> 00:55:05.100
But at no point -- certainly
not in Late Antiquity --

00:55:05.100 --> 00:55:08.970
were Christianity and Europe
perfectly coterminous.

00:55:08.970 --> 00:55:12.950
Nevertheless, Caucasia's early
Christianization has been widely

00:55:12.950 --> 00:55:19.010
interpreted as an immutable bade
of Caucasia's connection to Europe.

00:55:19.010 --> 00:55:23.090
Both assumptions had been
retrojected to remote times.

00:55:23.090 --> 00:55:26.720
And when I mean remote,
I mean a long time ago.

00:55:26.720 --> 00:55:30.810
The extraordinary discovery at
the Mona see in Southern Georgia

00:55:30.810 --> 00:55:34.110
of the oldest examples of Homo
erectus discovered outside

00:55:34.110 --> 00:55:38.760 position:56%
of Africa are frequently
identified as the earliest Georgians

00:55:38.760 --> 00:55:42.050
and as the very first Europeans.

00:55:42.050 --> 00:55:46.920 position:56%
But words like Georgian and European
had absolutely no historical meaning

00:55:46.920 --> 00:55:50.140
1.8 million years ago.

00:55:50.140 --> 00:55:53.110 position:56%
But let us return to Late Antiquity.

00:55:53.110 --> 00:55:56.690
There is no historical basis
to treat Christian and European

00:55:56.690 --> 00:56:00.010
as synonyms in Late
Antiquity from about the 2nd

00:56:00.010 --> 00:56:03.200
through the 8th Centuries
A.D. Furthermore,

00:56:03.200 --> 00:56:06.470
Christianization did not
necessarily entail integration

00:56:06.470 --> 00:56:08.880
to the Romano/Byzantine universe.

00:56:08.880 --> 00:56:12.830
What is frequently called
the Byzantine Commonwealth.

00:56:12.830 --> 00:56:14.130
In the case of Caucasia,

00:56:14.130 --> 00:56:17.310
Christianization certainly
enabled more robust bonds

00:56:17.310 --> 00:56:21.220
with Constantinople and
the Byzantine world.

00:56:21.220 --> 00:56:24.470
But Caucasia's existing
sociocultural fabric --

00:56:24.470 --> 00:56:27.170
one that had been woven
back in the Iron Age --

00:56:27.170 --> 00:56:31.680
remained fundamentally unaltered
as a result of Christianization.

00:56:31.680 --> 00:56:37.580
And this social fabric belonged
principally to the Iranian world.

00:56:37.580 --> 00:56:42.840
Thus, as Caucasia's indigenous
Zoroastrianism's were displaced

00:56:42.840 --> 00:56:46.940
across the 5th and 6th
Centuries, many other Iranian

00:56:46.940 --> 00:56:50.250
and Irenic were -- or if you
prefer Persianate aspects

00:56:50.250 --> 00:56:53.820
of Caucasian society
remained intact.

00:56:53.820 --> 00:56:57.910
And did so throughout
the premodern era.

00:56:57.910 --> 00:57:01.890
So, Caucasia was not so much
a space between the Iranian

00:57:01.890 --> 00:57:05.120
and Romano Byzantine
worlds, an exotic frontier

00:57:05.120 --> 00:57:10.050
between civilizations, nor was
it chiefly a passive bridge

00:57:10.050 --> 00:57:11.690
spanning them.

00:57:11.690 --> 00:57:17.030
Instead, starting under the Acumens
and through the early modern era,

00:57:17.030 --> 00:57:21.370
Caucasia was an integral component
of the Iranian cultural world.

00:57:21.370 --> 00:57:24.400
The broadest meaning of Iranshahr.

00:57:24.400 --> 00:57:25.700
This was a very big garden.

00:57:25.700 --> 00:57:30.190
It was very diverse and had
a lot of lovely flowers.

00:57:30.190 --> 00:57:32.990
Caucasia was a dynamic
and contributing member

00:57:32.990 --> 00:57:35.800
of the cross-cultural Iranian
commonwealth stretching

00:57:35.800 --> 00:57:38.920
from Central Eurasia --
Central Asia to Anatolia,

00:57:38.920 --> 00:57:41.540
and south to the Horn of Africa.

00:57:41.540 --> 00:57:45.370 position:56%
Across the breadth of Late Antiquity
even after Christianization,

00:57:45.370 --> 00:57:47.680
Caucasia's peoples
were firmly embedded

00:57:47.680 --> 00:57:50.660 position:56%
in the diverse Iranian commonwealth.

00:57:50.660 --> 00:57:54.420
In Late Antiquity, the Iranian
and especially Irenic features

00:57:54.420 --> 00:57:58.370
of Caucasian society
account for regional cohesion

00:57:58.370 --> 00:58:01.950
at least as much As Christianity.

00:58:01.950 --> 00:58:05.740
In any case, from its inception
Christianity fit itself

00:58:05.740 --> 00:58:08.780
to an assortment of
sociocultural frameworks

00:58:08.780 --> 00:58:11.460
but not just the Greco Roman.

00:58:11.460 --> 00:58:14.900
In Caucasia, this framework
was the Iranian world.

00:58:14.900 --> 00:58:18.550
Now so as to better
illustrate these points,

00:58:18.550 --> 00:58:21.420
let's turn to some
contemporary voices.

00:58:21.420 --> 00:58:22.760
I shall make reference this morning

00:58:22.760 --> 00:58:25.390
to the following histiographical
narratives used

00:58:25.390 --> 00:58:27.850
in Late Antique Caucasia.

00:58:27.850 --> 00:58:31.710
First, the Armenian narrative
of King Khosrov's conversion,

00:58:31.710 --> 00:58:36.030
the source attributed to the 5th
Century writer called Agat'angelos.

00:58:36.030 --> 00:58:37.330
Another Armenian text,

00:58:37.330 --> 00:58:42.270
the 5th Century <i>Buzandaran pat
mutiwnk </i>or <i>The Epic Histories </i>.

00:58:42.270 --> 00:58:46.780
The composite history of the land
of Albania written in Armenian

00:58:46.780 --> 00:58:50.450
and credited to Movses Dasxuranc'i.

00:58:50.450 --> 00:58:53.700
And two anonymous Georgian
histories;

00:58:53.700 --> 00:58:57.280
<i>The Life of the Kings </i>and <i>The
Life of Vaxtang Gorgasali </i>.

00:58:57.280 --> 00:58:59.620
The received forms of both
of these text are based

00:58:59.620 --> 00:59:03.710
on a lost Georgian source
from the 6th Century.

00:59:03.710 --> 00:59:06.880
Now according to all of
these Caucasian sources,

00:59:06.880 --> 00:59:09.940
the social landscape of Late
Antique Caucasia was characterized

00:59:09.940 --> 00:59:14.900
by an Irenic pattern dominated
by Dynastic aristocratic houses

00:59:14.900 --> 00:59:18.990
and a super aristocratic family
laying claim to royal status

00:59:18.990 --> 00:59:21.100
and the possession of the Farat.

00:59:21.100 --> 00:59:22.640
Royal glory.

00:59:22.640 --> 00:59:26.920
Significantly in Caucasia,
Bishops -- Christian Bishops,

00:59:26.920 --> 00:59:31.600 position:56%
fit their ecclesiastical authority
not to Roman or Roman like provinces

00:59:31.600 --> 00:59:34.620
and capitals -- which
did not exist here,

00:59:34.620 --> 00:59:38.410
but to the prevailing
noble and royal estates.

00:59:38.410 --> 00:59:43.400 position:56%
Early Bishops in Caucasia held their
post by hereditary right in harmony

00:59:43.400 --> 00:59:45.660
with the social practice
of the Iranian world

00:59:45.660 --> 00:59:49.140
and certainly not according
to Roman practice.

00:59:49.140 --> 00:59:52.590
Thus, in Armenia the family
of Gregory the Illuminator,

00:59:52.590 --> 00:59:55.680
the holy man who ensured
King Khosrov's baptism

00:59:55.680 --> 00:59:58.560
in the 4th Century,
monopolized the position

00:59:58.560 --> 01:00:03.040
of Chief Prelate of Armenia Major.

01:00:03.040 --> 01:00:05.030
The integration of
early Caucasian bishops

01:00:05.030 --> 01:00:09.820
within Iranshahr was manifest
in numerous other ways.

01:00:09.820 --> 01:00:11.710 position:56%
These Christian leaders were clothed

01:00:11.710 --> 01:00:15.050
in the heroic vocabulary
of the Iranian epic.

01:00:15.050 --> 01:00:19.360
A tradition enjoying tremendous
popularity throughout Caucasia.

01:00:19.360 --> 01:00:24.240
The epic history thusly describes
mid-Century Yusik the first,

01:00:24.240 --> 01:00:26.950 position:56%
grandson of Gregory the Illuminator.

01:00:26.950 --> 01:00:30.720
And I quote, "Yusik
followed the apostolic ways

01:00:30.720 --> 01:00:36.500
of his father Vrt'anes, and was a
son like unto his father's measure.

01:00:36.500 --> 01:00:40.890 position:56%
Altogether, in all things and in all
ways, he showed his angelic traits,

01:00:40.890 --> 01:00:42.590
and accomplished everything
in accordance

01:00:42.590 --> 01:00:45.400
with the grace granted
to him by God.

01:00:45.400 --> 01:00:48.660
He pastured the rational
Christian folk and admonished it

01:00:48.660 --> 01:00:51.320
with evangelical precepts.

01:00:51.320 --> 01:00:56.340
For he was young in years -- manure
-- victorious, tall in stature,

01:00:56.340 --> 01:01:00.230
with a face of wondrous beauty
and grace, so that no other

01:01:00.230 --> 01:01:03.390
like him could be found
anywhere on earth.

01:01:03.390 --> 01:01:07.250
Pure and resplendent in spirit,
he in no way concerned himself

01:01:07.250 --> 01:01:10.960
with things here below, but
from the days of his youth,

01:01:10.960 --> 01:01:16.390
like a valiant armored soldier of
Christ, like a heroic champion --

01:01:16.390 --> 01:01:22.160
nahadog, he defied and threatened
with victory the invisible foe.

01:01:22.160 --> 01:01:25.920
He had no knowledge of partiality
or of the respect of persons,

01:01:25.920 --> 01:01:31.260
but bore the world of the Holy
Spirit like a sword at his side.

01:01:31.260 --> 01:01:35.360
Yusik's Iranian presentation
is no aberration."

01:01:35.360 --> 01:01:40.630
In the Armenian <i>Epic Histories </i>,
such imagery reaches a crescendo

01:01:40.630 --> 01:01:44.660
in the panegyric of
[inaudible] the first.

01:01:44.660 --> 01:01:48.760
Narses was the great-great-grandson
of Gregory the Illuminator

01:01:48.760 --> 01:01:52.670
and the son of the Armenia
[inaudible] princess Bando Shin.

01:01:52.670 --> 01:01:56.770
An obvious transcription of the
Middle Raining word for Queen.

01:01:56.770 --> 01:01:59.470
Bishops like Yusik
and Narses were deemed

01:01:59.470 --> 01:02:03.150
to be epic heroes of
the Iranian kind.

01:02:03.150 --> 01:02:06.710
What's more, Narses
represents the biological fusion

01:02:06.710 --> 01:02:09.450
of the powerful ecclesiastical
dynastic elite --

01:02:09.450 --> 01:02:12.860
the Gregorites, and the
political rulers, the Arshakuni

01:02:12.860 --> 01:02:16.060
or the Armenia Arsichids
in a Christianizing,

01:02:16.060 --> 01:02:19.430
yet profoundly Irenic society.

01:02:19.430 --> 01:02:22.530
As we would expect, Iranian

01:02:22.530 --> 01:02:27.180
and Irenic heroic imagery is
also applied to Caucasian kings

01:02:27.180 --> 01:02:30.610
and their champion warriors
called [inaudible] in Armenian

01:02:30.610 --> 01:02:34.380
and [inaudible] in Georgian.

01:02:34.380 --> 01:02:37.040
Christianization did
not reverse this trend.

01:02:37.040 --> 01:02:39.980
Indeed, precisely as
result of Christianization,

01:02:39.980 --> 01:02:44.130
the Irenic epic tradition was
reinvigorated in Caucasia.

01:02:44.130 --> 01:02:48.110
Not only in Armenia, a
subject extensively studied

01:02:48.110 --> 01:02:50.390 position:56%
by Nina Garsyona [assumed spelling].

01:02:50.390 --> 01:02:53.380
Here let us consider the
history of Agat'angelos

01:02:53.380 --> 01:02:57.840
which describes the conversion
of King Khosrov to Christianity.

01:02:57.840 --> 01:03:02.740
Agat'angelos Armenia text commences
with the Sasanian overthrow

01:03:02.740 --> 01:03:04.040
of the parteon [inaudible].

01:03:04.040 --> 01:03:08.780
At the time [inaudible]
Hosrove II ruled in Armenia.

01:03:08.780 --> 01:03:13.670
He was the scion of the Aermenia
Arsicad or Arshakuni House

01:03:13.670 --> 01:03:17.050
and was the father of
the future King Terdod.

01:03:17.050 --> 01:03:20.220
The Armenian Hosrove was
determined to exact vengeance

01:03:20.220 --> 01:03:23.820
for the Sasanian [inaudible]
in Iran.

01:03:23.820 --> 01:03:28.710
According to Agat'angelos, the
time of the Parthian kingdom came

01:03:28.710 --> 01:03:33.870 position:56%
to an end when sovereignty was taken
away from Artawan son of Vatars

01:03:33.870 --> 01:03:37.970
on his murder by Artasir
son of Sasan.

01:03:37.970 --> 01:03:41.040
The latter was a prince from the
Province of Stahr who had come

01:03:41.040 --> 01:03:45.400
and united the forces of the
Persians; then they abandoned,

01:03:45.400 --> 01:03:49.710
rejected, and disdained the
sovereignty of the Parthians

01:03:49.710 --> 01:03:53.730
and happily chose the sovereignty
of Artasir son of Sasan.

01:03:53.730 --> 01:03:58.300
Now the sad news -- and this
is what is called sad news

01:03:58.300 --> 01:04:01.680
of the Parthians plight reached
the Aremenia [inaudible] king

01:04:01.680 --> 01:04:05.770
and at the start of the
next year King Hosrove began

01:04:05.770 --> 01:04:08.580
to raise forces and
assemble an army.

01:04:08.580 --> 01:04:12.080
He gathered the armies of the
Albanians and the Georgians,

01:04:12.080 --> 01:04:15.750
opened the Gates of the Alans
and the [inaudible] of Cor,

01:04:15.750 --> 01:04:18.890
and brought through the
army of the Huns in order

01:04:18.890 --> 01:04:22.750
to attack Persian territory
and invade Asorestan as far

01:04:22.750 --> 01:04:24.810
as the gates of Ctesiphon.

01:04:24.810 --> 01:04:26.790
He ravaged the whole country,

01:04:26.790 --> 01:04:30.100
ruining the populous
cities and prosperous towns.

01:04:30.100 --> 01:04:34.910
He attempted to eradicate,
destroy completely, extirpate

01:04:34.910 --> 01:04:39.440
and overthrow Persian
-- that is Sasanian --

01:04:39.440 --> 01:04:43.520
kingdom, and aimed at
abolishing its institutions.

01:04:43.520 --> 01:04:47.450
At the same time, he made an oath
to seek vengeance with great rancor

01:04:47.450 --> 01:04:50.270
for their loss of sovereignty.

01:04:50.270 --> 01:04:54.830 position:56%
So as to emphasize the uncompromised
legitimacy of the Parthians

01:04:54.830 --> 01:04:59.110
and the blatant theft of the
authority by the upstart Sasanians,

01:04:59.110 --> 01:05:02.630
some variants of Agat'angelos
incorporate the Parthian romance

01:05:02.630 --> 01:05:04.580
of Arthavan and Arthashir.

01:05:04.580 --> 01:05:09.730 position:56%
In Late Antiquity, the obsession
with dynastic honor and vengeance is

01:05:09.730 --> 01:05:15.430
as much a hallmark of the Iranian
as it is of Caucasian society.

01:05:15.430 --> 01:05:17.870
Throughout Caucasia this was
bolstered by the prevalence

01:05:17.870 --> 01:05:21.850
of royal families having
strong Parthian roots.

01:05:21.850 --> 01:05:26.620 position:56%
A circumstance persisting long after
the ascendency of the Sasanians.

01:05:26.620 --> 01:05:30.170
Significantly dynasties descended
from Parthian [inaudible]

01:05:30.170 --> 01:05:34.940 position:56%
and [inaudible] monopolized all
three throes of Caucasia at the time

01:05:34.940 --> 01:05:38.570
of their Christianization
in the 4th Century.

01:05:38.570 --> 01:05:43.510
Earlier Armenian histiography
highlights the unqualified royal

01:05:43.510 --> 01:05:50.290
legitimacy of the Armenian
Arshakuni's even

01:05:50.290 --> 01:05:54.190
when specific individuals
fell short in their duties.

01:05:54.190 --> 01:05:57.490
All the while, it cast
Arshakuni kingship

01:05:57.490 --> 01:06:01.140
in the familiar terms
of the Iranian world.

01:06:01.140 --> 01:06:02.630
Following an Armenia led victory

01:06:02.630 --> 01:06:10.020
of the Romans the [inaudible] II
reportedly acclaimed the Armenian

01:06:10.020 --> 01:06:11.320
[inaudible] in this manner.

01:06:11.320 --> 01:06:16.070
"The king of Armenia with his
own might has been our champion

01:06:16.070 --> 01:06:18.850
and he has performed a
deed of such valor --

01:06:18.850 --> 01:06:23.980
[inaudible] that no one else
by any means may perform it.

01:06:23.980 --> 01:06:26.770
However, relations with
[inaudible], were soured

01:06:26.770 --> 01:06:29.620
and [inaudible] invaded Armenia.

01:06:29.620 --> 01:06:31.210
In this tense atmosphere,

01:06:31.210 --> 01:06:35.520
the Armenia <i>Epic Histories</i>
repeatedly established Arshakuni

01:06:35.520 --> 01:06:39.050
validity through the
supposed actions and words

01:06:39.050 --> 01:06:41.410
of the Sasanian's themselves.

01:06:41.410 --> 01:06:44.090
Arshakuni burial sites
were especially targeted

01:06:44.090 --> 01:06:46.270
by Sasanian generals.

01:06:46.270 --> 01:06:48.770
Now the sad thing of such sites
would have immortalized the

01:06:48.770 --> 01:06:53.050
Armenians, but in its
account of the Iranian defeat

01:06:53.050 --> 01:06:55.600
in the central district of Ararat,

01:06:55.600 --> 01:06:59.500
the <i>Epic Histories</i>
reveals another objective.

01:06:59.500 --> 01:07:02.640
And the Armenians put all of them
to the sword, and they took away

01:07:02.640 --> 01:07:04.520
from them the bones
of their own kings

01:07:04.520 --> 01:07:08.810 position:56%
that the Persians were carrying away
into captivity to the Persian realm.

01:07:08.810 --> 01:07:12.860 position:56%
For they said, according to their
heathen beliefs: "This is the reason

01:07:12.860 --> 01:07:15.930
that we are taking the bones of
the Armenian kings to our realm:

01:07:15.930 --> 01:07:19.550
that the glory of the kings
and the fortune and valor

01:07:19.550 --> 01:07:23.570
of this realm might go from
here with the bones of the kings

01:07:23.570 --> 01:07:26.550
and entire into our realm."

01:07:26.550 --> 01:07:30.810
Needless to say, these supernatural
attributes, P'ark, baxt,

01:07:30.810 --> 01:07:35.050
k'ajut iwn -- glory,
fortune, and valor are pillars

01:07:35.050 --> 01:07:38.830
of kingship not just in
Armenia, but throughout Caucasia

01:07:38.830 --> 01:07:42.890
and the entire Iranian world.

01:07:42.890 --> 01:07:46.760
Georgian sources apply
equivalent Irenic imagery

01:07:46.760 --> 01:07:50.670
to both Zoroastrian
and Christian monarchs.

01:07:50.670 --> 01:07:55.900
The most striking Christian example
is Vakhtang I Gorgasali who ruled

01:07:55.900 --> 01:07:58.400
at the turn of the
5th and 6th Centuries.

01:07:58.400 --> 01:08:01.550
The narrative anchor of
the text known as <i>The Life</i>

01:08:01.550 --> 01:08:06.940
<i>of [inaudible] </i>is a series of
single combats waged by Vakhtang.

01:08:06.940 --> 01:08:11.480
This Christian hero king worsted
in turn a Hazar named Tarkan,

01:08:11.480 --> 01:08:17.250
an Alan named Bakatar, a Christian
Byzantine Logotheit named Poly

01:08:17.250 --> 01:08:21.380
Carpos and an unnamed
king of Sendia.

01:08:21.380 --> 01:08:24.770
Although always taking pains
to credit his royal legitimacy

01:08:24.770 --> 01:08:27.390
and physical prowess
to the Christian god,

01:08:27.390 --> 01:08:30.070
Vakhtang is never made to
enter into single combat

01:08:30.070 --> 01:08:33.030
against Zoroastrian Iranians.

01:08:33.030 --> 01:08:38.950
However, under Vakhtang's command,
were many loyal Iranian champions.

01:08:38.950 --> 01:08:42.580
The Irenic imagery enshrouding the
Christian Vakhtang is particularly

01:08:42.580 --> 01:08:45.450 position:56%
evident in a squirmish with Bakatar.

01:08:45.450 --> 01:08:47.810
A titian hailing from
Northern Caucasia,

01:08:47.810 --> 01:08:50.550
the region known as Alania.

01:08:50.550 --> 01:08:53.490
And this passage was
worth quoting in full.

01:08:53.490 --> 01:08:56.790
So, you get a sense of
this Iranian type imagery.

01:08:56.790 --> 01:09:02.650
"Baqat'ar was a giant, a goliat
I, and since the time he had begun

01:09:02.650 --> 01:09:06.800
to engage in combat no one had
been able to resist him in battle,

01:09:06.800 --> 01:09:09.810
and he had killed all
of his adversaries.

01:09:09.810 --> 01:09:13.320 position:56%
This Baqat'ar stood on the bank of
a river and shouted in a loud voice,

01:09:13.320 --> 01:09:17.180
" Oh King Vaxtang, do not be
proud of your killing of Tarq'an.

01:09:17.180 --> 01:09:21.550
He was not one of the giants and
therefore he was slain by a youth."

01:09:21.550 --> 01:09:25.570
Then King Vaxtang replied
to Baqat'ar saying,

01:09:25.570 --> 01:09:28.160
"No only through my own
strength did I overcome T'arq'an,

01:09:28.160 --> 01:09:30.360
but through the strength
of my Creator.

01:09:30.360 --> 01:09:32.540
For the power of Christ is with me,

01:09:32.540 --> 01:09:35.070
and his honorable cross
is my armor."

01:09:35.070 --> 01:09:37.970
He mounted his horse, which
was covered with chain armor,

01:09:37.970 --> 01:09:43.080 position:56%
he took up his shield of tiger-skin,
which a sword could not cut.

01:09:43.080 --> 01:09:46.520
Baqat'ar crossed the river
and began to shoot arrows.

01:09:46.520 --> 01:09:49.720
By the sharpness of his eyes,
the keenness of his mind,

01:09:49.720 --> 01:09:53.890
and the agility of his horse
Vaxtang avoided the arrows.

01:09:53.890 --> 01:09:56.230
On both sides, the
sounds of trumpets

01:09:56.230 --> 01:09:58.950
and drums rose from the troops.

01:09:58.950 --> 01:10:02.020
Baqat'ar was not able to
shoot more than two arrows

01:10:02.020 --> 01:10:04.360
at Vaxtang's shield,
and he did not hit it.

01:10:04.360 --> 01:10:09.410
Then he shot another arrow at
Vaxtang's horse which penetrated.

01:10:09.410 --> 01:10:12.600
While his horse was falling
Vaxtang rushed on Baqat'ar,

01:10:12.600 --> 01:10:14.480
brought his sword down
on his shoulders

01:10:14.480 --> 01:10:16.490
and penetrated to his heart.

01:10:16.490 --> 01:10:18.660 position:56%
At that moment Vaxtang's horse fell.

01:10:18.660 --> 01:10:23.310
He quickly put out his hand
and grasped Baqat'ar's horse.

01:10:23.310 --> 01:10:25.890
First, he fell to the
ground, worshipped God,

01:10:25.890 --> 01:10:28.560
and blessed him even
more than before.

01:10:28.560 --> 01:10:32.490
Although we don't have
time to explore it today,

01:10:32.490 --> 01:10:34.580
the potent Irenic imagery found

01:10:34.580 --> 01:10:39.190
in Caucasian text has abundant
visual parallels as well.

01:10:39.190 --> 01:10:42.060
Most notably is in
the spread wings motif

01:10:42.060 --> 01:10:47.800
that has been specially
studied by Matteo Compareti.

01:10:47.800 --> 01:10:52.260
Now, as a conclusion, I would like
to offer a few words about tensions

01:10:52.260 --> 01:10:54.850
between Parthian's and Sasanian's.

01:10:54.850 --> 01:10:57.210
It goes without saying
that the Sasanian regime

01:10:57.210 --> 01:11:02.060
in many ways depended upon
Parthian elements in Iran.

01:11:02.060 --> 01:11:08.350
In Caucasia, where Caucasia
Parthian royalty remained in place,

01:11:08.350 --> 01:11:12.600
heavy-handed Sasanian tactics
operated alongside measures

01:11:12.600 --> 01:11:16.630
fostering mutual confidence
and corporative governance.

01:11:16.630 --> 01:11:21.070
The history of Albania reports
that Shapur II made an effort

01:11:21.070 --> 01:11:24.910
to identify subject peoples who
should be honored in his court.

01:11:24.910 --> 01:11:28.650
The status of the Armenians
had come into doubt

01:11:28.650 --> 01:11:31.960
and the [inaudible] presented
them with an ultimatum.

01:11:31.960 --> 01:11:36.790
Demonstrate through "an ancient
book Armenian noble status,

01:11:36.790 --> 01:11:44.000
lest it tells us prized cushions be
conferred upon Audian aristocrats."

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:47.790
The Armenian thereafter
presented Sapur with a manuscript

01:11:47.790 --> 01:11:51.600
of Agat'angelos' history, which
the King of Kings "Commanded

01:11:51.600 --> 01:11:57.200
to be translated into the Persian
language and script when he learned

01:11:57.200 --> 01:12:02.400 position:56%
that it commenced with Artasir, his
own forefather, he rejoiced greatly,

01:12:02.400 --> 01:12:06.850
and moved to tears he praised the
book and held it before his eyes."

01:12:06.850 --> 01:12:09.790
Finding therein the figure
of seventeen cushions,

01:12:09.790 --> 01:12:12.050
he began to arrange
accordingly the seats

01:12:12.050 --> 01:12:14.150
of everyone at the royal table.

01:12:14.150 --> 01:12:18.840
Now should this reflect a genuine
event we can only conjecture

01:12:18.840 --> 01:12:24.660
about the version of Agat'angelos'
presented to the Sasanian empower,

01:12:24.660 --> 01:12:27.910
the surviving Armenian
variant mentions Articshir only

01:12:27.910 --> 01:12:30.710
in connection with the
subjugation of Parthian

01:12:30.710 --> 01:12:34.950
and Parthius fall is
openly lamented here.

01:12:34.950 --> 01:12:38.730 position:56%
The Greek version of
Agat'angelos' uniquely preserves the

01:12:38.730 --> 01:12:44.090
aforementioned Parthian romance
expounding upon the last Parthian

01:12:44.090 --> 01:12:46.760
[inaudible] Artivan and the
rise to power of Articshir.

01:12:46.760 --> 01:12:51.350
But it can hardly be termed
as a pro-Sasanian tract.

01:12:51.350 --> 01:12:54.470
In light of the considerable
reworking of Agat'angelos' cycle

01:12:54.470 --> 01:12:58.430
across Late Antiquity it would
not however been difficult

01:12:58.430 --> 01:13:01.300
for Armenian [inaudible]
to modify the narrative

01:13:01.300 --> 01:13:04.220
so as to win Shapur's favor.

01:13:04.220 --> 01:13:10.490
And so, if one looks beyond
the triumph of Christianity,

01:13:10.490 --> 01:13:14.830
much of the surviving Agat'angelos'
tradition would have resonated

01:13:14.830 --> 01:13:18.530
with the Sasanian's and other
Iranians for that matter.

01:13:18.530 --> 01:13:21.010
For it repeated political
and social modes

01:13:21.010 --> 01:13:23.710
that circulated throughout
the Iranian world,

01:13:23.710 --> 01:13:27.360
including the heartland
of Iran itself.

01:13:27.360 --> 01:13:31.670
And this I think is the ultimate
image of Late Antique Caucasia.

01:13:31.670 --> 01:13:36.060
Not as some hinge between
the mythical East and West,

01:13:36.060 --> 01:13:40.820
but as a Christianizing Irenic
society firmly implanted

01:13:40.820 --> 01:13:42.690
in the Iranian commonwealth.

