And how do we end up there?

01:18:40.710 --> 01:18:44.240
And my narrative starts
at the top of the slide.

01:18:44.240 --> 01:18:49.290
The 484 with the Death of Peroz
the Sasanian king in a battle

01:18:49.290 --> 01:18:50.590
against the Hephthalites.

01:18:50.590 --> 01:18:52.710
One of the Barbarians
mentioned over there,

01:18:52.710 --> 01:18:54.450
which are not in their own opinion

01:18:54.450 --> 01:18:58.290
that Barbarian nor are
they outside the boundaries

01:18:58.290 --> 01:19:01.440
of Iranshahr as Touraj mentioned.

01:19:01.440 --> 01:19:04.640
Oxus to Euphrates is a
very useful way of thinking

01:19:04.640 --> 01:19:08.260
about the Sasanian
Empire or the Arianshir

01:19:08.260 --> 01:19:11.910
from their own particularly
ideological point of view,

01:19:11.910 --> 01:19:15.300
but as I have mostly argued
in the book and I will try

01:19:15.300 --> 01:19:19.930
to touch upon today, the
people over there do not think

01:19:19.930 --> 01:19:23.410
of themselves necessarily
as outside that boundary.

01:19:23.410 --> 01:19:27.740
My basic argumentation for
that, which I channeled to dwell

01:19:27.740 --> 01:19:33.130
on too much today, is the fact that
they call themselves [inaudible]

01:19:33.130 --> 01:19:36.580
of the king calling
himself [inaudible].

01:19:36.580 --> 01:19:38.570
The Kind of [inaudible].

01:19:38.570 --> 01:19:43.190 position:56%
This [inaudible] is not the province
that you're thinking of today

01:19:43.190 --> 01:19:47.960
in East Iran, nor is
the Islamic [inaudible].

01:19:47.960 --> 01:19:53.060
It is actually a Middle Persian
translation of the [inaudible]

01:19:53.060 --> 01:19:55.790 position:56%
which means where the sun comes out.

01:19:55.790 --> 01:19:58.640
The East. The King of the East.

01:19:58.640 --> 01:20:00.290
Of course there is a lot east

01:20:00.290 --> 01:20:05.530
of what this people
consider themselves.

01:20:05.530 --> 01:20:06.830
[Inaudible] desert.

01:20:06.830 --> 01:20:08.130
And China, and well Japan,

01:20:08.130 --> 01:20:10.520
and if you just go East
enough you get to California.

01:20:10.520 --> 01:20:12.270
So they are not the
East of anywhere.

01:20:12.270 --> 01:20:13.570
But they are the East

01:20:13.570 --> 01:20:17.420
of this Iranshahr they're
imagining themselves to be.

01:20:17.420 --> 01:20:20.180
And that is one of the
main arguments they have,

01:20:20.180 --> 01:20:24.420
that beyond the Oxus and
beyond things that we think

01:20:24.420 --> 01:20:28.760
of as the boundaries of Iranshahr
people did consider themselves part

01:20:28.760 --> 01:20:30.490
of this greater entity.

01:20:30.490 --> 01:20:35.760 position:56%
And as we see, it is beyond Oxus in
the early Islamic period where a lot

01:20:35.760 --> 01:20:39.850
of this culture that we
recognize as a Persian culture

01:20:39.850 --> 01:20:44.650
or what we recognize as even the
Persian language actually gets --

01:20:44.650 --> 01:20:45.950
matures up.

01:20:45.950 --> 01:20:48.610
So just think of the
fact that the first poets

01:20:48.610 --> 01:20:52.260
of Persian language
lived beyond Oxus

01:20:52.260 --> 01:20:55.010
through [inaudible] for example.

01:20:55.010 --> 01:20:57.210
So these are the people
who are actually

01:20:57.210 --> 01:21:00.330
between the Juxoraties
and the Euphrates.

01:21:00.330 --> 01:21:04.970
So the people around and beyond
these boundaries actually end

01:21:04.970 --> 01:21:09.630
up being the best caretakers of the
culture that we are thinking about.

01:21:09.630 --> 01:21:14.850
Now, this whole event
starts here in this period.

01:21:14.850 --> 01:21:18.540
I can't point to it, but as
you can see, the big blue blob

01:21:18.540 --> 01:21:21.470
in the middle is called
the Hephthalites Empire.

01:21:21.470 --> 01:21:28.570
And the Hephthalites come to
existence a little before 484.

01:21:28.570 --> 01:21:33.500
That king [inaudible] Touraj was
mentioning establishes his lands is

01:21:33.500 --> 01:21:38.980
probably a Sasanian reiteration
or maybe reinterpretation

01:21:38.980 --> 01:21:41.230
of what is actually
happening during the time

01:21:41.230 --> 01:21:44.790
of the famous Sasanian
King Baphomet IV.

01:21:44.790 --> 01:21:49.640
Or Bahome [inaudible] the
one who hunts [inaudible],

01:21:49.640 --> 01:21:56.110
who really establishes a
tower at the border and says

01:21:56.110 --> 01:21:58.740
that the other side is
your empire, your kingdom,

01:21:58.740 --> 01:22:00.040
whatever you want to call it.

01:22:00.040 --> 01:22:01.340
The Hephthalites.

01:22:01.340 --> 01:22:02.650
And this side is my kingdom.

01:22:02.650 --> 01:22:05.490
So these Hephthalites however
are not very fond of that

01:22:05.490 --> 01:22:07.500
and neither is the Sasanian king.

01:22:07.500 --> 01:22:11.550
A series of squirmishes from
the 470's on finally results

01:22:11.550 --> 01:22:13.780
in a disaster for the Sasanians,

01:22:13.780 --> 01:22:19.120
which is the death of
[inaudible] in 484.

01:22:19.120 --> 01:22:25.400
In a very carefully planned line
of defense by the Hephthalites.

01:22:25.400 --> 01:22:30.990
These Hephthalites are
the latest wave of what

01:22:30.990 --> 01:22:38.040
in German the great
[inaudible] the Iranian Huns.

01:22:38.040 --> 01:22:41.750
I rather use the German one
because when you get to English,

01:22:41.750 --> 01:22:43.050
to Huns, you think of Attila.

01:22:43.050 --> 01:22:46.850
I want people to not
think of Attila.

01:22:46.850 --> 01:22:51.650
So the Hephthalites
are of this group

01:22:51.650 --> 01:22:53.890
and they have formed
a Kingdome over there.

01:22:53.890 --> 01:22:59.080
And in 484 when they managed to
kill [inaudible] they really become

01:22:59.080 --> 01:23:01.870
for a good 20 years the people

01:23:01.870 --> 01:23:06.520
who call the shots on
the Sasanian Empire.

01:23:06.520 --> 01:23:10.100
We have them in the
later Islamic sources as,

01:23:10.100 --> 01:23:14.050
oh the Sasanian King comes and
he gets removed by his nobles

01:23:14.050 --> 01:23:16.270
and the other one comes,
and then the new one comes.

01:23:16.270 --> 01:23:19.110
But they all end up in
the Hephthalites court.

01:23:19.110 --> 01:23:23.380
Including [inaudible] son
Kevat [assumed spelling],

01:23:23.380 --> 01:23:28.040
who he gets removed
supposedly and the accusation

01:23:28.040 --> 01:23:30.920
of promoting masochism he
goes to the Hephthalites court

01:23:30.920 --> 01:23:32.720
and then gets reinstalled.

01:23:32.720 --> 01:23:36.840
Not by saying that he was
wrong about the masochism --

01:23:36.840 --> 01:23:40.830
if any of it existed -- but by
help of the Hephthalites army.

01:23:40.830 --> 01:23:45.460
In 498 he actually
takes his crown back.

01:23:45.460 --> 01:23:50.390
And other than their political
allegiance Sasanians pay

01:23:50.390 --> 01:23:53.270
Hephthalites a lot of money.

01:23:53.270 --> 01:23:55.580
Bob Schoff [assumed spelling]
should like these pictures.

01:23:55.580 --> 01:24:01.830
So the Hephthalites are actually
getting the coins of Peroz on top

01:24:01.830 --> 01:24:03.780
and making their own version of it.

01:24:03.780 --> 01:24:07.560
As you can see, they don't really
care about inscriptions that much.

01:24:07.560 --> 01:24:09.260
They just copy the coins.

01:24:09.260 --> 01:24:15.020 position:56%
So, there's a lot of money going
from Iran, going from this Iranshahr

01:24:15.020 --> 01:24:19.180
to the Hephthalites territories and
well they are very happy about it.

01:24:19.180 --> 01:24:21.390
I think what happens here is

01:24:21.390 --> 01:24:25.210
that this peripheral
power centrality ends

01:24:25.210 --> 01:24:31.190 position:56%
up forcing the Sasanians to
finally have their eyes on the West.

01:24:31.190 --> 01:24:33.610
Now, this might sound
strange to many of you.

01:24:33.610 --> 01:24:36.740
We usually know of the
Sasanians from Western sources.

01:24:36.740 --> 01:24:43.290
We know of Sasanians through
Roman, and later Islamic sources.

01:24:43.290 --> 01:24:46.560
All of whom talk about the West
inside of the Sasanian Empire.

01:24:46.560 --> 01:24:51.930
And it seems like the Sasanians
are a very Western oriented power.

01:24:51.930 --> 01:24:54.120
In reality, when you
look at the sources,

01:24:54.120 --> 01:24:56.130
Sasanians are quite
an Eastern power.

01:24:56.130 --> 01:25:00.870
Most of the preoccupation of
the Sasanians in the first half

01:25:00.870 --> 01:25:03.750
of their rule is their
Eastern borders.

01:25:03.750 --> 01:25:06.020
The biggest campaigns
are in the East.

01:25:06.020 --> 01:25:08.460
I'm not necessarily going to
stress the point too much,

01:25:08.460 --> 01:25:10.290
but I think the fact that
they put their capital

01:25:10.290 --> 01:25:12.740
on the very West means
that's the place

01:25:12.740 --> 01:25:15.140
that they felt the safest about.

01:25:15.140 --> 01:25:17.490
They felt the unsafest in the East.

01:25:17.490 --> 01:25:20.640
That is my suggestion
of the whole thing.

01:25:20.640 --> 01:25:23.440
But starting in the
restoration of Kavat

01:25:23.440 --> 01:25:30.620
in 498 this Western attention
becomes a major point

01:25:30.620 --> 01:25:31.920
for the Sasanians.

01:25:31.920 --> 01:25:36.260
They have to take on the
Western borders more seriously

01:25:36.260 --> 01:25:39.690
and by the way, extract any
resources from it they can.

01:25:39.690 --> 01:25:42.180
Because they owe Hephthalites
a lot of money

01:25:42.180 --> 01:25:43.850
and they have already
paid quite a bit of it.

01:25:43.850 --> 01:25:48.740
So, from 502 you have the
start of a series of wars.

01:25:48.740 --> 01:25:51.870
It starts from a war
in 502 to 504 known

01:25:51.870 --> 01:25:55.130
in Roman sources as
the Anestasian Wars.

01:25:55.130 --> 01:25:57.440
And these are all of the wars.

01:25:57.440 --> 01:26:01.720
You can see the different lines
and they all continue until 628.

01:26:01.720 --> 01:26:05.670
So it's not a continuous war,
but on and off for the rest

01:26:05.670 --> 01:26:11.750
of the Sasanian reign you have a
series of wars between Sasanians

01:26:11.750 --> 01:26:14.880
and Byzantines, often
at a standstill.

01:26:14.880 --> 01:26:18.940
Sometimes with upper hand for
the Sasanians and less often

01:26:18.940 --> 01:26:23.440
for the Byzantines until
the Arabs/Muslims come.

01:26:23.440 --> 01:26:27.810
And these wars continue and they
seem to generate a good amount

01:26:27.810 --> 01:26:31.440
of money, but also a
good amount of impetus

01:26:31.440 --> 01:26:33.340
for reorganization of the empire.

01:26:33.340 --> 01:26:36.730
This reorganization is
known as the Reforms.

01:26:36.730 --> 01:26:41.760
Attributed popularly to
Hosrove I, but less popularly

01:26:41.760 --> 01:26:44.580
and probably more accurately
to Kavat,

01:26:44.580 --> 01:26:49.530
which results in a complete
revamping of the taxation system.

01:26:49.530 --> 01:26:53.170
As you say IRS is always
at the forefront

01:26:53.170 --> 01:26:55.080
of every change that we have.

01:26:55.080 --> 01:27:00.720
So the Sasanians change their
taxation system as well.

01:27:00.720 --> 01:27:07.390
There is a complete redoing of the
military system and less studied

01:27:07.390 --> 01:27:13.350
and still underway, a complete
redoing of their social

01:27:13.350 --> 01:27:19.140
and known structure of the
Sasanian nobility particularly.

01:27:19.140 --> 01:27:21.600
These things as I said,
are usually attributed

01:27:21.600 --> 01:27:24.970
to the gentleman here, Shapur I.

01:27:24.970 --> 01:27:26.270
Obviously one of them is a coin.

01:27:26.270 --> 01:27:30.640
The other one is a famous relief
on the wall of the House of Justice

01:27:30.640 --> 01:27:34.690
or the Hall of Justice in Tehran.

01:27:34.690 --> 01:27:37.460
[Inaudible] as I'm
sure most of you know,

01:27:37.460 --> 01:27:41.250
is known as the [inaudible]
or then The Just.

01:27:41.250 --> 01:27:47.370
And is the example of justice
in the Sasanian period.

01:27:47.370 --> 01:27:55.070
And he is also continues all of
these wars and goes on to take

01:27:55.070 --> 01:28:01.800 position:56%
over most of the areas that had been
controlled by the Sasanians prior

01:28:01.800 --> 01:28:05.790
to the start of the wars,
and slowly expands East.

01:28:05.790 --> 01:28:09.390
So going back to that map.

01:28:09.390 --> 01:28:13.270
In the West he runs a
series of conquests.

01:28:13.270 --> 01:28:16.330
he is rather successful
gains the Byzantines.

01:28:16.330 --> 01:28:17.840
Not necessarily all the time,

01:28:17.840 --> 01:28:21.990
but he does establish his Western
borders, including trade towns.

01:28:21.990 --> 01:28:27.700
And further in the East he finally
in about 670 -- is mean 570 --

01:28:27.700 --> 01:28:33.080
we don't really have the date,
he with the help of the Western

01:28:33.080 --> 01:28:37.050
or the [inaudible] manages
to destroy the Hephthalites.

01:28:37.050 --> 01:28:38.350
So those Hephthalites for --

01:28:38.350 --> 01:28:41.280
who about 80 years ago
had determined the fate

01:28:41.280 --> 01:28:44.130
of the Sasanian Empire
are now broken down

01:28:44.130 --> 01:28:47.500
and their territory is incorporated

01:28:47.500 --> 01:28:50.160
into the territories
of the Sasanians.

01:28:50.160 --> 01:28:52.580
How effective that is and who takes

01:28:52.580 --> 01:28:55.120
over what is a matter
of controversy.

01:28:55.120 --> 01:28:58.530 position:56%
But we do know that at least as sort

01:28:58.530 --> 01:29:01.520
of the central power
Hephthalites don't exist anymore.

01:29:01.520 --> 01:29:04.710
They might exist in smaller
Hephthalites entities

01:29:04.710 --> 01:29:11.400
up to the coming of
the Muslim armies.

01:29:11.400 --> 01:29:15.540
In this -- oops, so
after this event,

01:29:15.540 --> 01:29:24.340
the Sasanian Empire has formed
itself as an expanding power.

01:29:24.340 --> 01:29:27.650
It has secured its Western borders.

01:29:27.650 --> 01:29:32.900
It has now defeated its greatest
enemy in the West -- in the East.

01:29:32.900 --> 01:29:40.460 position:56%
And has created this empire
divided into four military divisions

01:29:40.460 --> 01:29:42.400
of [inaudible] in the East,
[inaudible] in the West,

01:29:42.400 --> 01:29:46.770
Naruz's in the South, and
usually called [inaudible]

01:29:46.770 --> 01:29:48.920
or [inaudible] in the North.

01:29:48.920 --> 01:29:53.150
It has established a
good taxation system

01:29:53.150 --> 01:29:56.340
and it doesn't necessarily
seem to be very happy

01:29:56.340 --> 01:29:57.640
with the state of affairs.

01:29:57.640 --> 01:29:59.570
It still wants to expand.

01:29:59.570 --> 01:30:01.420
Particularly in the West.

01:30:01.420 --> 01:30:05.700
And that happens with
the succession --

01:30:05.700 --> 01:30:08.490
troublesome succession
of Hosrove II.

01:30:08.490 --> 01:30:12.650
I didn't mention one of the kings
[inaudible], but it's pointless

01:30:12.650 --> 01:30:16.710
to go through his reign
at this time.

01:30:16.710 --> 01:30:21.100
Hosrove II in 590 becomes the king.

01:30:21.100 --> 01:30:25.960
He's almost immediately
removed by one of his generals,

01:30:25.960 --> 01:30:31.500
the famous [inaudible]
who initially has him flee

01:30:31.500 --> 01:30:35.070
to the Byzantine Empire.

01:30:35.070 --> 01:30:38.410
The various and mostly
Roman and later Islamic --

01:30:38.410 --> 01:30:41.680
Midevil Islamic sources say
that he goes to Constantinople

01:30:41.680 --> 01:30:44.720
and he marries the daughter
of the Roman empower.

01:30:44.720 --> 01:30:47.060
Probably mythological.

01:30:47.060 --> 01:30:51.260
he does go to Syria
though and he does get help

01:30:51.260 --> 01:30:53.370
from Morris [assumed
spelling] the Roman emperor.

01:30:53.370 --> 01:30:58.790
Comes back -- this is the scene
from a midevil Persian manuscript

01:30:58.790 --> 01:31:05.190 position:56%
of [inaudible] on the left side of
the river fighting Hosrove's troops.

01:31:05.190 --> 01:31:06.740
So [inaudible] for a year rules.

01:31:06.740 --> 01:31:13.190
591 Hosrove comes back and
starts establishing himself.

01:31:16.330 --> 01:31:23.650
And shortly after that he seems
to find the perfect excuse to go

01:31:23.650 --> 01:31:26.000
on with his expansionist ideas.

01:31:26.000 --> 01:31:28.660
And his expansionist ideas
as I said, are the West.

01:31:28.660 --> 01:31:32.160
So from 602 he starts his
campaigns in the West.

01:31:32.160 --> 01:31:38.050 position:56%
Now, the main motivation is that in
602 his Roman Patron Emperor Morris,

01:31:38.050 --> 01:31:44.050
the one who helped him
succeed, has been killed by one

01:31:44.050 --> 01:31:46.070
of his own nobles called
Focus [assumed spelling].

01:31:46.070 --> 01:31:51.620
And this gives enough
reason to Hosrove to want

01:31:51.620 --> 01:31:55.970
to take revenge for Morris' death.

01:31:55.970 --> 01:31:59.670
So then from 602 he starts
conquering in the West.

01:31:59.670 --> 01:32:03.270
As you can see from the map, he
takes over very quickly the area

01:32:03.270 --> 01:32:06.070
of Anatolia, most of Syria.

01:32:06.070 --> 01:32:10.120
he goes down towards
Palestine and in a second phase

01:32:10.120 --> 01:32:14.930
after 613 he starts
taking over Egypt as well.

01:32:14.930 --> 01:32:16.460
Now, why is this important?

01:32:16.460 --> 01:32:21.860
Well other than the fact that it's
a very cool event, it is the fact

01:32:21.860 --> 01:32:28.180
that he is taking over most of the
areas to the North of the lands

01:32:28.180 --> 01:32:30.720
where Islam initially
comes to existence.

01:32:30.720 --> 01:32:37.930
Notice, time is 613 to 628;
621 is the date of Hedgra.

01:32:37.930 --> 01:32:41.680
So, when Mohamed is moving
from Mecca to Medina,

01:32:41.680 --> 01:32:45.170
when the Islamic states
-- the first version of it

01:32:45.170 --> 01:32:52.730
in Medina is forming -- Sasanians
have taken over the passage

01:32:52.730 --> 01:32:57.010
that the Arabs have to the rest
of the world from the North.

01:32:57.010 --> 01:33:02.180
They are in Syria and they are
surrounding the Arabs on the North

01:33:02.180 --> 01:33:05.420
and even on the Northwest in Egypt.

01:33:05.420 --> 01:33:11.230
Now, this scene is the scene of
the defeat of Hosrove at the hand

01:33:11.230 --> 01:33:14.930
of Heraclius in [inaudible].

01:33:14.930 --> 01:33:20.950
And he gets in one of the
most interesting regicides

01:33:20.950 --> 01:33:22.250
in world history.

01:33:22.250 --> 01:33:24.790
He gets removed --
he's also put on trial.

01:33:24.790 --> 01:33:29.960
There is an official complaint
about him from the court.

01:33:29.960 --> 01:33:31.260
He answers it.

01:33:31.260 --> 01:33:33.190
He -- we have it in [inaudible],

01:33:33.190 --> 01:33:35.390
we have it in [inaudible],
we have it everywhere.

01:33:35.390 --> 01:33:38.290
And his defense is not
accepted and he sort

01:33:38.290 --> 01:33:41.880
of is executed/someone
is allowed to kill him.

01:33:41.880 --> 01:33:44.210
So they send someone to kill him.

01:33:44.210 --> 01:33:49.000
So in 628 Hosrove II is killed,
the Sasanian Empire falls

01:33:49.000 --> 01:33:52.800
into a terrible state of
disarray and I would suggest

01:33:52.800 --> 01:33:55.500
that this is the end
of the Sasanian Empire.

01:33:55.500 --> 01:33:58.120
This is the end of the
Sasanian Dynasty for sure.

01:33:58.120 --> 01:34:03.460 position:56%
What happens after this is really of
little significance and what comes

01:34:03.460 --> 01:34:07.010
up after it is really an
internal dynastic fight.

01:34:07.010 --> 01:34:08.890
The empire is done for.

01:34:08.890 --> 01:34:12.880
The empire is -- the lands --
Iranshahr is going its own way.

01:34:12.880 --> 01:34:18.720
And culturally and politically,
economically it is already

01:34:18.720 --> 01:34:22.560
on the way to becoming what we
recognize as in the midevil period

01:34:22.560 --> 01:34:26.070
as the land of the [inaudible],
the land of the forced,

01:34:26.070 --> 01:34:28.050
the land of the Persians.

01:34:28.050 --> 01:34:32.000
And -- but before we get there
we have to notice that the power

