01:50:38.120 --> 01:50:41.790
The killing of the Prophet
Mani, the eponymous founder

01:50:41.790 --> 01:50:44.820
of the Manichaeism religion
in the 3rd Century was one

01:50:44.820 --> 01:50:47.460
of the most discussed
events in late antiquity.

01:50:47.460 --> 01:50:52.420
From being labeled a heretic,
lunatic, seducer, maniac,

01:50:52.420 --> 01:50:54.900
pseudo prophet, and
my personal favorite,

01:50:54.900 --> 01:50:59.020
a nimble-fingered thief do amene
[inaudible] sensitive treatment

01:50:59.020 --> 01:51:01.740
of Mani in his novel
<i>The Gardens of Light </i>.

01:51:01.740 --> 01:51:05.140
Mani's fascinating life and
gruesome death have long captured

01:51:05.140 --> 01:51:07.720
our imaginations.

01:51:07.720 --> 01:51:10.940
As you can see the number one
on the projector, Ibn al-Nadim,

01:51:10.940 --> 01:51:14.000
the great Muslim scholar
of the 10th Century stated,

01:51:14.000 --> 01:51:17.180
Mani was put to death during
the reign of Bahram b. Sabur.

01:51:17.180 --> 01:51:20.790
After he executed him he
suspended him in two pieces,

01:51:20.790 --> 01:51:24.450 position:56%
one half over a certain gate and
the other half over a different gate

01:51:24.450 --> 01:51:26.530
of the city of Junday sabur.

01:51:26.530 --> 01:51:29.340
These two places received the
designations 'the upper part

01:51:29.340 --> 01:51:31.800
of the Lord' and 'the
lower part of the Lord'.

01:51:31.800 --> 01:51:34.650
It is said that he has been
previously imprisoned by Sabur,

01:51:34.650 --> 01:51:37.750
but after Sabur died
Bahram feed him.

01:51:37.750 --> 01:51:39.650
It is also said that he
died while in prison,

01:51:39.650 --> 01:51:43.450
but there is no uncertainty
regarding his crucifixion.

01:51:43.450 --> 01:51:45.620
This highly evocative description

01:51:45.620 --> 01:51:49.100 position:56%
of Mani's ultimate demise
beautifully captures the dilemmas we

01:51:49.100 --> 01:51:51.530
scholars face while
studying the Sasanians.

01:51:51.530 --> 01:51:54.240
Since all of our narrative
historical sources

01:51:54.240 --> 01:51:56.870
for Iranian religious
history were either written

01:51:56.870 --> 01:52:00.470
by the much later Muslim scholars
writing Arabic and Persian

01:52:00.470 --> 01:52:03.110
or we have to be content with the
histories and chronicles written

01:52:03.110 --> 01:52:06.820
by their traditional enemies,
the Romans and Byzantines.

01:52:06.820 --> 01:52:12.370
Or Christian communities composed
of former Zoroastrians writing

01:52:12.370 --> 01:52:15.680
in Syriac and of course the
underappreciated sources Armenia

01:52:15.680 --> 01:52:16.980
and Georgia.

01:52:16.980 --> 01:52:19.490
I might have left out
the Jewish sources.

01:52:19.490 --> 01:52:20.790
Apologies.

01:52:20.790 --> 01:52:23.450
What we do have in the way
of securely datable sources

01:52:23.450 --> 01:52:27.840
from the actual Sasanian period
are royal inscriptions and reliefs,

01:52:27.840 --> 01:52:30.360
coins, seals, bullae, and papyri.

01:52:30.360 --> 01:52:32.570 position:56%
All of which reflect forms of a rich

01:52:32.570 --> 01:52:35.280
and varied Zoroastrian
political theology.

01:52:35.280 --> 01:52:39.480
But that typically do not formally
explicate their own symbolism

01:52:39.480 --> 01:52:41.870
in a self-reflective manner.

01:52:41.870 --> 01:52:45.150
What I would like to do today is
to show you how the hermeneutical

01:52:45.150 --> 01:52:47.860
or interpretive traditions
in Zoroastrian Middle Persia

01:52:47.860 --> 01:52:51.960 position:56%
or Palative literature are redacted
in the early Islamic period has much

01:52:51.960 --> 01:52:54.080
to contribute to a
richer understanding

01:52:54.080 --> 01:52:56.170
of Sasanian historiography.

01:52:56.170 --> 01:53:00.330
I will do so by showcasing how the
Manicheans writing in Parthian,

01:53:00.330 --> 01:53:02.780
the Zoroastrians producing
hermeneutical legal

01:53:02.780 --> 01:53:05.510
and polemical texts in
Palatian [inaudible],

01:53:05.510 --> 01:53:09.250
and the Islamic heraseyographers
writing in Arabic all made meaning

01:53:09.250 --> 01:53:12.530
of the death of Mani at
the hands of Behram I.

01:53:12.530 --> 01:53:17.410
In my opinion, no figure better
embodied the cosmopolitanism

01:53:17.410 --> 01:53:19.990
of the Sasanian world than Mani.

01:53:19.990 --> 01:53:23.880
As the founder of the world's first
truly universalizing religion,

01:53:23.880 --> 01:53:27.930
Mani claimed to be inheritor of
prophets like Jesus, the Buddha,

01:53:27.930 --> 01:53:31.690
and Zarathustra, all the while
joined from traditions associated

01:53:31.690 --> 01:53:35.830
with biblical patriarchs
such Seth, Noah, and Enoch.

01:53:35.830 --> 01:53:40.220
And apostles like Paul, upon
whom Mani modeled his church.

01:53:40.220 --> 01:53:42.140
Echoing the title of my talk,

01:53:42.140 --> 01:53:46.920
let us begin by looking beyond
the Sasanian realm to the East.

01:53:46.920 --> 01:53:50.970
As you can see in slide number
two in lines one through four,

01:53:50.970 --> 01:53:54.970 position:56%
in a Manichaean/Parthian text on the
death of Mani from the Turfan oasis

01:53:54.970 --> 01:54:00.310 position:56%
in Western China, we find references
to his [inaudible] or par nirvana.

01:54:00.310 --> 01:54:03.090
A Buddhist term signifying
a blessed state of death

01:54:03.090 --> 01:54:07.000
in which the deceased is freed from
the cycle of birth and rebirth.

01:54:07.000 --> 01:54:11.130
And I quote, "And he Mani
was unconscious and died.

01:54:11.130 --> 01:54:16.750
Such was the parinirvana of our
father, as this is written."

01:54:16.750 --> 01:54:21.580
The religious and cultural
cosmopolitanism

01:54:21.580 --> 01:54:25.420 position:56%
of this text is once again
showcased in lines seven through ten

01:54:25.420 --> 01:54:27.400
when the Manichaean's -- sorry --

01:54:27.400 --> 01:54:31.900
when the Manichaean's referred
to their Lord and Messiah

01:54:31.900 --> 01:54:33.650
as [inaudible] or crucifixion.

01:54:33.650 --> 01:54:38.930
And I quote, "When as we all know
as for when Jesus to the Messiah

01:54:38.930 --> 01:54:41.300
of us all, the Lord was crucified."

01:54:41.300 --> 01:54:44.210 position:56%
Here in the text we find the
Manichaean's also drawing upon their

01:54:44.210 --> 01:54:46.110
inherited Christian symbolism.

01:54:46.110 --> 01:54:49.670
Thus equating Mani's death at the
hands of the Sasanians with that

01:54:49.670 --> 01:54:53.360
of a prophetic forerunner,
namely Jesus' ultimate sacrifice.

01:54:53.360 --> 01:54:56.400
East truly meets West.

01:54:56.400 --> 01:55:00.490 position:56%
In Sasanian studies, Mani's death is
discussed most often in conjunction

01:55:00.490 --> 01:55:05.120 position:56%
with the Zorastrin imperial response
to ethnoreligious diversity found

01:55:05.120 --> 01:55:07.600
in the contemporaneous
3rd Century reliefs

01:55:07.600 --> 01:55:09.880
of the Zorastrin high
priest Caridier.

01:55:09.880 --> 01:55:17.580
Who unabashedly states, "And Jews,
Buddhists, Hindus, Nazarenes,

01:55:17.580 --> 01:55:20.740
Christians, Baptists,
and Manichaean's/zandig

01:55:20.740 --> 01:55:23.490
within the realm were struck
down idols were destroyed,

01:55:23.490 --> 01:55:25.410
dwellings of the demons
were ruined and turned

01:55:25.410 --> 01:55:28.050
into thrones and seats
for the gods."

01:55:28.050 --> 01:55:30.390
This passage has been
discussed ad naseum,

01:55:30.390 --> 01:55:31.940
especially since it is right here

01:55:31.940 --> 01:55:34.230
that we have the first
attestation of the term zandig.

01:55:34.230 --> 01:55:37.180
Later used by Muslims
for the Manichaean's.

01:55:37.180 --> 01:55:42.430
What is far less well-known however
is the explicitly isogenic act

01:55:42.430 --> 01:55:47.020
of reading the death of Mani into
the gothos or forms of Zarathustra

01:55:47.020 --> 01:55:50.030
in the hermeneutical tradition
in [inaudible] literature.

01:55:50.030 --> 01:55:53.310
The text in question is the
9th book of the Denkard,

01:55:53.310 --> 01:55:58.660
the largest extent Palative text,
estimated at some 170,000 words.

01:55:58.660 --> 01:56:01.890
Denkard book nine purports
to be a [inaudible] resume

01:56:01.890 --> 01:56:05.260
of a lost Palavey translation,
commentary or zand

01:56:05.260 --> 01:56:10.400 position:56%
of a putative [inaudible] commentary
or mask on the old evestan gothos.

01:56:10.400 --> 01:56:15.250
Basically, we have stage one
from mid-second millennium BCE.

01:56:15.250 --> 01:56:21.890 position:56%
An stage four from the early 11th
Century C.E. some 2,500 years later.

01:56:21.890 --> 01:56:24.080
While the myriad issues
of textual transmission

01:56:24.080 --> 01:56:27.220
and interpretive fidelity
are beyond our scope today,

01:56:27.220 --> 01:56:29.950
what should interest us is not
just the fact that the gothos

01:56:29.950 --> 01:56:33.290
from two millennia earlier were
read as having something to say

01:56:33.290 --> 01:56:35.960
about a major sociopolitical event,

01:56:35.960 --> 01:56:38.840
rather it is the isogenical
technique of reading

01:56:38.840 --> 01:56:42.620
into the gothos here which
is particularly fascinating.

01:56:42.620 --> 01:56:49.060 position:56%
And the passage in Denkard 9 states,
and about the sign of Mani crippled

01:56:49.060 --> 01:56:51.920
by the lie and the wicked
hearers -- niyosag --

01:56:51.920 --> 01:56:54.600
of his, and the beating which
came upon him from the Lord

01:56:54.600 --> 01:56:57.040
of the Land -- presumably Behram I.

01:56:57.040 --> 01:57:01.100
And this too, he is wicked who
gives my world to the vengeful one,

01:57:01.100 --> 01:57:04.540
Ahrimen, he will have raised
up the wound demon himself.

01:57:04.540 --> 01:57:07.410
That is, he will have been
set in motion for the death

01:57:07.410 --> 01:57:09.600
of the world of the Righteous.

01:57:09.600 --> 01:57:12.600
The text then goes on to
quote Mani as having boasted,

01:57:12.600 --> 01:57:14.910
"I am better suited for the -- "

01:57:19.370 --> 01:57:21.670
"I am better suited
for the office of Rad

01:57:21.670 --> 01:57:23.500
and the office of the Dastwar.

01:57:23.500 --> 01:57:27.300
With the Denkard text consequently
critiquing Mani by stating,

01:57:27.300 --> 01:57:29.960
but that is not the
way Zarduxst did it.

01:57:29.960 --> 01:57:32.970
He -- Mani -- makes
men devour mutrisn."

01:57:32.970 --> 01:57:34.270
Something like filth.

01:57:34.270 --> 01:57:36.380
And he says to them, eternal life.

01:57:36.380 --> 01:57:38.550
That is, there is eternal
life from it for those

01:57:38.550 --> 01:57:41.370
who were made to devour mutrisn.

01:57:41.370 --> 01:57:44.730
Then they think, the
sacrifice the demons is best.

01:57:44.730 --> 01:57:48.410
Besides the rather opaque
traditional inter-significations

01:57:48.410 --> 01:57:51.610
used by the Zoroastrian
priests as weapons of polemic,

01:57:51.610 --> 01:57:53.150
how and why is Mani found

01:57:53.150 --> 01:57:55.760
in the gothic commentary
in the first place?

01:57:55.760 --> 01:57:58.140 position:56%
What line, formula, word, or concept

01:57:58.140 --> 01:58:01.570
in the original sacred scriptures
motivates this isogenical

01:58:01.570 --> 01:58:03.450
textual practice?

01:58:03.450 --> 01:58:07.280
The second millennia BCE,
gothic [inaudible] base text

01:58:07.280 --> 01:58:10.410
that triggers this radical
interpretation appears

01:58:10.410 --> 01:58:15.630
to be Yasna 46.7, which is part
of Zartrush [inaudible] complaint

01:58:15.630 --> 01:58:19.190
as he was facing persecution
and a lack of social acceptance.

01:58:19.190 --> 01:58:23.450
And I quote, "But whom do you
appoint as guardian for one

01:58:23.450 --> 01:58:26.960
such as me, O Mazda, when
the deceitful one tries

01:58:26.960 --> 01:58:29.900
to seize me in order to injure me."

01:58:29.900 --> 01:58:38.640 position:56%
And Zarathustra then adds in Yasna
46.8, if someone who places my herds

01:58:38.640 --> 01:58:42.880
through sin, may destruction not
reach me through his actions.

01:58:42.880 --> 01:58:48.120
May it, in response, come upon him
for that hostility onto his body.

01:58:48.120 --> 01:58:52.800
The gothic text here in line with
its epidictic genre of praise

01:58:52.800 --> 01:58:57.080
and blame poetry, that is
praise God and score evil,

01:58:57.080 --> 01:58:58.790
suggests that the poet priest --

01:58:58.790 --> 01:59:01.500
presumably Zarathustra and
his priestly followers --

01:59:01.500 --> 01:59:05.520
will not be held liable for the
misdeeds of the wicked ones.

01:59:05.520 --> 01:59:09.900
The late antique [inaudible]
to translation come commentary

01:59:09.900 --> 01:59:14.540
of these ancient Avestan
scriptures renders this as he --

01:59:14.540 --> 01:59:18.930
presumably Mani -- who gives my
world to that vengeful one --

01:59:18.930 --> 01:59:20.660
[inaudible] -- he gives
away property

01:59:20.660 --> 01:59:22.950
to the authority of the heretics.

01:59:22.950 --> 01:59:27.820 position:56%
here, the world or [inaudible], that
is modern [inaudible] is glossed

01:59:27.820 --> 01:59:31.930
by the concept of property or
[inaudible] and it is given away

01:59:31.930 --> 01:59:35.580
through the authority or power
of the heretics of ahlomoyan,

01:59:35.580 --> 01:59:39.560
understood in Denkard book nine to
be none other than the Manichaean's

01:59:39.560 --> 01:59:43.470
who were notorious for their
renunciations of philosophy.

01:59:43.470 --> 01:59:48.240
And a little later in Pahlavi of
Yasna 46.8, we find it stated,

01:59:48.240 --> 01:59:51.240
to the bodies of the
heretics and the man --

01:59:51.240 --> 01:59:53.290
presumable Mani, the ruler comes.

01:59:53.290 --> 01:59:56.460
That is, he takes retribution
on them.

01:59:56.460 --> 02:00:00.060
What we have here is
truly fascinating.

02:00:00.060 --> 02:00:03.570
Bronze Age references to moveable
property or herds and the lack

02:00:03.570 --> 02:00:08.190
of social acceptance of an archaic
priestly poet sacrificer are

02:00:08.190 --> 02:00:12.790
allegorically re-tasked in the late
antique and early Islamic contexts,

02:00:12.790 --> 02:00:17.370
and subsequently understood as a
scriptural proof or justification

02:00:17.370 --> 02:00:21.480
for two actual historical events
in the early Sasanian period.

02:00:21.480 --> 02:00:24.730
One, the renunciation of
property by the Manichaeans,

02:00:24.730 --> 02:00:28.210
and the subsequent seizure of
their property by the Sasanians.

02:00:28.210 --> 02:00:34.630 position:56%
And two, the killing of Mani by
Bahram I in 274 C.E. For the seizure

02:00:34.630 --> 02:00:38.480
of Manichaean property, we can
once again look beyond the Sasanian

02:00:38.480 --> 02:00:43.550
world, this time to the West, to
legislation issued in 381 C.E.

02:00:43.550 --> 02:00:48.650
by the Roman Emperor Theodosius
in order to limit the philanthropy

02:00:48.650 --> 02:00:52.860
of Mani's hearers or auditories in
the -- for the benefit of the elect

02:00:52.860 --> 02:00:54.700
or electing of his church.

02:00:54.700 --> 02:00:59.430 position:56%
"If any Manichaean man or woman from
the day of the law enacted long ago,

02:00:59.430 --> 02:01:02.490
and originally by our parents,
has transmitted his own property

02:01:02.490 --> 02:01:06.120
to any person whatsoever, by
having made a will or under title

02:01:06.120 --> 02:01:09.790
of any liberality whatsoever,
or by form of donation,

02:01:09.790 --> 02:01:12.920
or if anyone of these persons
has been enriched by grant

02:01:12.920 --> 02:01:16.340
of an inheritance entered
through any form whatsoever,

02:01:16.340 --> 02:01:18.150
since immediately from
the said persons

02:01:18.150 --> 02:01:22.510
under branded infamy's perpetual
stigma, we withdraw all capability

02:01:22.510 --> 02:01:25.970
of making a will and of
living under Roman law.

02:01:25.970 --> 02:01:29.170
And since we do not permit them to
have the power either of leaving

02:01:29.170 --> 02:01:33.540
or taking any inheritance, the
whole by an immediate investigation

02:01:33.540 --> 02:01:37.710
on the part of our treasury,
should be joined to its resources."

02:01:37.710 --> 02:01:41.640
Just as we see in the West, we
can look within the Sasanian world

02:01:41.640 --> 02:01:45.320
for confirmation of these property
seizures by turning our gaze back

02:01:45.320 --> 02:01:49.410 position:56%
to the [inaudible] resources, namely
the "Madayan I Hazar Dadestan,"

02:01:49.410 --> 02:01:54.020
or "Book of a Thousand Judgments,"
a Sasarnian era law code.

02:01:54.020 --> 02:01:59.990 position:56%
It explicitly discusses the seizure
of property due to heresy, zandigih,

02:01:59.990 --> 02:02:03.190
a term most often associated with
the Manichaeans, as we saw earlier

02:02:03.190 --> 02:02:04.680
in [inaudible] inscription.

02:02:04.680 --> 02:02:09.280
The "Madayan" states, "The property
of the sorcerer, jadug xwastag,

02:02:09.280 --> 02:02:13.340
such as he has, when they firmly
establish his being a sorcerer,

02:02:13.340 --> 02:02:18.170
shall be held by the Rad," that
is the supreme priestly authority.

02:02:18.170 --> 02:02:21.230
In isolation, the passage I have
just cited is not absolutely

02:02:21.230 --> 02:02:23.870
probative, but the
"Madayan" then adds,

02:02:23.870 --> 02:02:27.250
"Heresy is sorcery,"
zandigih jadugih.

02:02:27.250 --> 02:02:31.830
And finally, it declaims, "Due
to practicing heresy," zandigih,

02:02:31.830 --> 02:02:34.210
"and following the
beliefs of the heretic,

02:02:34.210 --> 02:02:38.170
one's property is seized
for the treasury."

02:02:38.170 --> 02:02:40.500
So what do we have here in
terms of the relationship

02:02:40.500 --> 02:02:44.910
between Sasanian jurisprudence
administered largely by priests

02:02:44.910 --> 02:02:46.960
and the Zoroastrian
hermeneutical tradition,

02:02:46.960 --> 02:02:49.670
also produced by the
priesthood, in a different sector

02:02:49.670 --> 02:02:51.200
of the knowledge economy?

02:02:51.200 --> 02:02:53.740
From the perspectives of
the emic, or traditional,

02:02:53.740 --> 02:02:55.910
interpreters of a religious
tradition,

02:02:55.910 --> 02:02:57.850
in this case the [speaking
in foreign language],

02:02:57.850 --> 02:03:01.700
their only obligation was to
make meaning, produce theology,

02:03:01.700 --> 02:03:04.840
by grappling with the profound
hermeneutical challenge

02:03:04.840 --> 02:03:08.700
of constantly enlivening their
received past of archaic myth

02:03:08.700 --> 02:03:11.680
and ritual from the
[inaudible] world.

02:03:11.680 --> 02:03:14.280
I would argue that they
did so assiduously,

02:03:14.280 --> 02:03:18.170
using tradition-constituted
forms of allegoresis,

02:03:18.170 --> 02:03:21.030
what I colloquially call
Zoroastrian thought,

02:03:21.030 --> 02:03:25.500
to speak to their contemporary
social realities by expanding,

02:03:25.500 --> 02:03:28.870
not delimiting, the
spiritual and semantic range

02:03:28.870 --> 02:03:30.680
of scriptural understanding.

02:03:30.680 --> 02:03:34.120
For them, just as it was
for the rabbis, scripture,

02:03:34.120 --> 02:03:39.200
in this case the "Avesta," spoke
for an already-encoded all forms

02:03:39.200 --> 02:03:42.430
of lived human experience
within human history

02:03:42.430 --> 02:03:46.130
and cosmic temporality,
including all future religious

02:03:46.130 --> 02:03:47.960
and political events.

02:03:47.960 --> 02:03:50.010
The Manichaean challenge

02:03:50.010 --> 02:03:52.910
of an aggressively
inter-confessional nature was

02:03:52.910 --> 02:03:56.270
so threatening to the
Zoroastrian priesthood precisely

02:03:56.270 --> 02:04:00.320
because of Mani's promiscuous
borrowing form the theological

02:04:00.320 --> 02:04:03.670
terms, concepts, and deities
from the native Iranian

02:04:03.670 --> 02:04:10.440
that is Zoroastrian tradition,
as when Mani says, "Fourth,

02:04:10.440 --> 02:04:12.910
this revelation of the
two principles/origins,

02:04:12.910 --> 02:04:16.680
and my living books/scriptures,
wisdom, and knowledge, are more

02:04:16.680 --> 02:04:22.540
and better than those of the
religions of the ancients."

02:04:22.540 --> 02:04:27.490
The "Skand-gumanig Wizar," a tenth
century polemic on the sorcery,

02:04:27.490 --> 02:04:30.590
jadugih, of Manichaean
doctrine, written in Pazand --

02:04:30.590 --> 02:04:33.360
that is, Middle Persian
written in the Avestan alphabet,

02:04:33.360 --> 02:04:35.640
with glosses added from
its Sanskrit version --

02:04:35.640 --> 02:04:42.100
states, "I have completely
escaped the doubt, and errors,

02:04:42.100 --> 02:04:46.440
and deceptions, and evil of the
false doctrines, and especially

02:04:46.440 --> 02:04:48.760
from the greatest deceiver,
the worst teacher,

02:04:48.760 --> 02:04:53.180
the airhead Mani whose
false doctrine is sorcery,

02:04:53.180 --> 02:04:56.870
and whose religion, din, is
deceit, and whose teaching is evil,

02:04:56.870 --> 02:05:00.270
and whose custom is
spread in secret."

02:05:00.270 --> 02:05:05.370
One person's esotericism is
another person's occultism.

02:05:05.370 --> 02:05:09.050
Al-Mas udi, living in tenth
century Baghdad, the precise place

02:05:09.050 --> 02:05:14.010
where the [inaudible] was written
some 60 years later, tells us,

02:05:14.010 --> 02:05:18.010
"We report that Mani, the son
of Yazid, disciple of Qardun,

02:05:18.010 --> 02:05:21.340
came to Bahram and presented
to him the dualist doctrines.

02:05:21.340 --> 02:05:24.350
He cunningly accepted them until
he had gathered his missionaries,

02:05:24.350 --> 02:05:27.420
who were dispersed across the
lands, those of his disciples

02:05:27.420 --> 02:05:30.040
who preached the dualist
doctrines to the people.

02:05:30.040 --> 02:05:31.630
Then he," that's Bahram,
"killed him,

02:05:31.630 --> 02:05:33.960
and he killed the leaders
of his disciples.

02:05:33.960 --> 02:05:36.850
The word zindiqa was
created in the days of Mani,

02:05:36.850 --> 02:05:39.130
with whom the zanadiqa
are associated.

02:05:39.130 --> 02:05:43.740
And regarding this, when Zaradusht
the son of Asbiman, spitaman,

02:05:43.740 --> 02:05:45.650
whose genealogy we
have already mentioned,

02:05:45.650 --> 02:05:49.540 position:56%
brought to the Persians a book
called the "Bista," that's "Avesta,"

02:05:49.540 --> 02:05:52.690
"in the first language of the
Persians, he gave it a commentary,

02:05:52.690 --> 02:05:55.080
tafsir, called the "Zand."

02:05:55.080 --> 02:06:02.000
And he gave this commentary
a gloss called "Bazand",

02:06:02.000 --> 02:06:03.740
Pazand, as we have said before.

02:06:03.740 --> 02:06:05.570
The "Zand" was an explanation

02:06:05.570 --> 02:06:08.910
for the esoteric/allegorical
interpretation, ta wil,

02:06:08.910 --> 02:06:10.820
of the ancient revelation.

02:06:10.820 --> 02:06:14.050
Whoever there was in their religion
who adduced anything in opposition

02:06:14.050 --> 02:06:16.600
to the revelation,
that is the "Bista,"

02:06:16.600 --> 02:06:20.700 position:56%
and who turned toward the
esoteric/allegorical interpretation,

02:06:20.700 --> 02:06:24.800
that is the "Zand," they would
say, "He is a zandi," referring

02:06:24.800 --> 02:06:27.840
to the name of the interpretation,
which shows that he had moved

02:06:27.840 --> 02:06:30.430
from the exoteric meanings
of the revelation

02:06:30.430 --> 02:06:32.860
to the esoteric interpretation.

02:06:32.860 --> 02:06:35.410
And this is in contradiction
to the revelation.

02:06:35.410 --> 02:06:38.550
When the Arabs came, they took
this term from the Persians,

02:06:38.550 --> 02:06:42.450
and they pronounced it
zindiq and Arabized it."

02:06:42.450 --> 02:06:45.370
While many of us have read this
passage and others like it as part

02:06:45.370 --> 02:06:49.310
of the Manichaean/Zandi question
connected to Islamic heresiography,

02:06:49.310 --> 02:06:54.470
I believe al-Mas udi is also
giving us an eyewitness proof,

02:06:54.470 --> 02:06:58.040
through Islamic eyes, no doubt,
of the very contested process

02:06:58.040 --> 02:07:00.850
of allegoresis within
the Zoroastrian tradition

02:07:00.850 --> 02:07:02.910
that I have been discussing today.

02:07:02.910 --> 02:07:05.920
We have largely ignored the
knowledge production of the quote,

02:07:05.920 --> 02:07:09.830
unquote Zoroastrian Zindiqs
because we, the philologists,

02:07:09.830 --> 02:07:12.350
as root etymological fetishizers,

02:07:12.350 --> 02:07:15.640
continue to perceive their
allegorical textual practices

02:07:15.640 --> 02:07:17.550
to be bad philology.

02:07:17.550 --> 02:07:21.560
I would contend that allegoresis --
that is the expansion of meaning --

02:07:21.560 --> 02:07:24.330
as knowledge from the [speaking in
foreign language] religion, or Den,

02:07:24.330 --> 02:07:26.740
was used as a defense
of the idealized view

02:07:26.740 --> 02:07:30.050
of the Sasanian status
quo and can best be seen

02:07:30.050 --> 02:07:34.600
in another [inaudible] passage
on heresy in "Denkard Book III"

02:07:34.600 --> 02:07:36.790
in a chapter entitled, "The
Protection of the Knowledge

02:07:36.790 --> 02:07:40.700
of the Religion, Den, from the
Destruction of the Heretics."

02:07:40.700 --> 02:07:43.410
"And one is the discernment by
the enumerators and teachers

02:07:43.410 --> 02:07:46.570 position:56%
of the religion from which comes the
protection of the proper knowledge

02:07:46.570 --> 02:07:49.780
of the religion from the
destruction of the heretics.

02:07:49.780 --> 02:07:52.140
In a truthful manner,
through good authority,

02:07:52.140 --> 02:07:55.050
there will be the going
forth of the religion," Den,

02:07:55.050 --> 02:07:57.330
"and through the arrangement
of kingship, xwadayih,

02:07:57.330 --> 02:08:00.230
there will be the management
of the world."

02:08:00.230 --> 02:08:03.630
Here we see the deployment of
a Sasanian theological trope

02:08:03.630 --> 02:08:06.860 position:56%
and [inaudible] much better known
from [speaking in foreign language],

02:08:06.860 --> 02:08:10.650
an Islamic political theory, from
none other than al-Mas uri himself

02:08:10.650 --> 02:08:14.040
and others, who commonly site
the founder of the Sasanians,

02:08:14.040 --> 02:08:19.380
Ardashir I, as saying,
"Religion, Den, and kingship, mulk,

02:08:19.380 --> 02:08:22.250
are two brothers, and neither
can dispense with the other.

02:08:22.250 --> 02:08:23.970
Religion is the foundation
of kingship,

02:08:23.970 --> 02:08:25.980
and kingship protects religion.

02:08:25.980 --> 02:08:28.360
For whatever lacks a
foundation must perish,

02:08:28.360 --> 02:08:31.630
and whatever lacks a
protector disappears."

02:08:31.630 --> 02:08:35.010
Mani and his followers'
cosmopolitanism threatened its

02:08:35.010 --> 02:08:38.320
highly idealized view of the
relationship between priestly

02:08:38.320 --> 02:08:40.730
and royal power in Sasanian Iran,

02:08:40.730 --> 02:08:44.600
so much so that the Sasanian
kings felt compelled to kill Mani,

02:08:44.600 --> 02:08:47.880
while the Zoroastrian priestly
counterparts felt equally compelled

02:08:47.880 --> 02:08:52.340
to mock and reject Mani's claims
to being a latter-day Zarathustra.

02:08:52.340 --> 02:08:56.260
And in doing so, ironically
enough, they immortalized him

02:08:56.260 --> 02:09:00.300 position:56%
as a persecuted prophet, and read
his ultimate device into the Gathas.

02:09:00.300 --> 02:09:02.100
Thank you.

02:09:02.100 --> 02:09:09.300
[ Applause ]

02:09:09.300 --> 02:09:11.150
