02:58:22.740 --> 02:58:26.030
I mean, he really is
the first person

02:58:26.030 --> 02:58:30.300
to make a truly universalizing
claim about religion.

02:58:30.300 --> 02:58:32.810
And he says this in one of
the texts that I cited --

02:58:32.810 --> 02:58:34.740
I had in the PowerPoint there.

02:58:34.740 --> 02:58:38.270
Essentially, mine is not
one religion for one people

02:58:38.270 --> 02:58:40.510
or one ethnicity, it's
for all peoples,

02:58:40.510 --> 02:58:42.570
and it's in all these languages.

02:58:42.570 --> 02:58:45.990
And so you see Manichaean
materials produced both East

02:58:45.990 --> 02:58:48.360
and West, all over the place.

02:58:48.360 --> 02:58:52.180
The thing that made
Manichaeism both brilliant

02:58:52.180 --> 02:58:55.950
and efficient also was the seeds of
its destruction, which is that --

02:58:55.950 --> 02:58:59.540
and I mean this with no
pejorative -- it is a sort of a --

02:58:59.540 --> 02:59:03.240
it has a sort of parasitic aspect
in that in every environment

02:59:03.240 --> 02:59:08.010
where it goes, it takes on the
guise of the local vocabulary,

02:59:08.010 --> 02:59:10.030
the traditions, the ideas.

02:59:10.030 --> 02:59:15.790
So it would be super-efficient
in the sense that everyone feels

02:59:15.790 --> 02:59:19.990
that they get to see themselves
in their own prior identities.

02:59:19.990 --> 02:59:22.620
They don't actually feel like
they're necessarily switching

02:59:22.620 --> 02:59:26.280
to something else, as getting
a more refined message.

02:59:26.280 --> 02:59:29.980
But therein lies the problem,
because from the imperial

02:59:29.980 --> 02:59:34.200
and religious elites everywhere,
East and West, this will look

02:59:34.200 --> 02:59:39.010
like a highly virulent sort of
heresy and things like that.

02:59:39.010 --> 02:59:40.460
And it's really interesting that --

02:59:40.460 --> 02:59:43.030
I mean, except for the
[inaudible] Turks, I mean,

02:59:43.030 --> 02:59:48.850 position:56%
everywhere else they were persecuted
